《'''山頂區保留條例'''》（{{lang-en|Peak District Reservation Ordinance}}）<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Peak District Ordinance, 1904|url=http://oelawhk.lib.hku.hk/archive/files/24f2010e0de63d845e7551701de18300.pdf|language=en|access-date=2014-01-22|archive-date=2021-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211105115944/https://oelawhk.lib.hku.hk/archive/files/24f2010e0de63d845e7551701de18300.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Lai">{{Cite book| last = Lai,| first = Lawrence Wai-Chung,| authorlink =| coauthors = Weicong Li, Ki Fong| title = Town Planning Practice: Context, Procedures and Statistics for Hong Kong| publisher = Hong Kong University Press| year = 2000| location = Hong Kong| pages =13| url = http://books.google.com/?id=pMikv58lxdIC&dq=%22Hill+District+Reservation%22| isbn =9789622095168 }}</ref>，原稱《'''山區保留條例'''》（{{lang|en|Hill District Reservation Ordinance}}）<ref>{{Cite web|title=《山區保留條例》全文|url=http://webb-site.com/codocs/HillDistrictReservationOrdinance.pdf|language=en|accessdate=2011-11-26|archive-date=2011-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004202456/http://webb-site.com/codocs/HillDistrictReservationOrdinance.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Council">{{cite press release| title = Council Sittiing Record of Legislative Council of Hong Kong| publisher = Legislative Council of Hong Kong| date = 1904-03-28| url = http://www.legco.gov.hk/1904/h040328.pdf| accessdate = 2008-08-14| archive-date = 2011-02-06| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110206031016/http://www.legco.gov.hk/1904/h040328.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Council"/>，是[[香港政府|香港政府]]以[[人種|種族]]為基礎而制定的土地用途法例，規定[[太平山_(香港)|太平山]]山頂區保留為非[[華人|華人]]的居住地，獲[[行政長官會同行政會議|總督會同行政局]]准許者除外<ref name="Council" /><ref name="Wilt">{{cite book |last=Wiltshire |first=Trea|title=Old Hong Kong|year=2003|orig-year=1987|volume=1|page=21|isbn=9627283606|publisher=Asia books Ltd.}}</ref>。

法例頒佈時值[[腺鼠疫|腺鼠疫]]{{tsl|en|Third plague pandemic|腺鼠疫第三次大流行|第三次瘟疫}}在中國爆發<ref name="Cohn 2003 336">{{Cite book|last=Cohn|first=Samuel K.|authorlink=|title=The Black Death Transformed: Disease and Culture in Early Renaissance Europe|publisher=A Hodder Arnold|year=2003|location=|page=[https://archive.org/details/blackdeathtransf00samu/page/336 336]|url=https://archive.org/details/blackdeathtransf00samu/page/336|isbn=0-340-70646-5}}{{registration}}</ref>，同時大批華人從北方湧入香港<ref>{{Citation|url=http://library.legco.gov.hk:1080/record=b1032135|title=Official Record of Proceedings, 1904.04.19.|accessdate=2018-08-07|publisher=[[香港立法會|Legislative Council of Hong Kong]]|year=1904|author=Legislative Council of Hong Kong|archive-date=2020-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200719122909/http://library.legco.gov.hk:1080/record=b1032135|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當代歷史學家對於港府制定法例的源由有不同意見<ref name="Jason">{{Cite book  | last = Wordie  | first = Jason  | title = Streets: Exploring Hong Kong Island| publisher = [[香港大學出版社|Hong Kong University Press]]  | year = 2002  | location = Hong Kong  | pages =74–75| isbn = 962-209-563-1 }}</ref>，主要可分為衛生隔離以及社會地位隔離<ref name="Wilt" />，後者包括保護殖民地官員和富商，以免出現恐慌。《立法局議事錄》記錄在二讀期間，兩名華人立法局議員[[何啟|何啟]]和[[韋寶珊|韋玉]]沒有反對，但社會中的少數「上流華人」則不滿法案<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legco.gov.hk/1904/h040419.pdf|title=Hansard for the Legislative Council meeting on 19 April 1904|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031224629/https://www.legco.gov.hk/1904/h040419.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

法例於1904年至1930年期間實施，[[何東|何東]]爵士是香港首位獲香港政府准許在山頂區居住的非歐籍人士<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.heritage.gov.hk/tc/doc/LegCo_Brief_Declaration_of_HTG_as_PM(C).pdf|title=根據《古物及古蹟條例》把山頂道75號何東花園宣布為暫定古蹟|accessdate=2018-07-22|author=古物諮詢委員會|date=2011-01-28|publisher=立法會|archive-date=2018-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722095944/https://www.heritage.gov.hk/tc/doc/LegCo_Brief_Declaration_of_HTG_as_PM(C).pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。類似的法例也曾經在[[長洲_(香港)|長洲]]實施。

== 背景 ==
=== 衛生層面 ===
1894年，[[腺鼠疫|腺鼠疫]][[第三次鼠疫大流行|第三波瘟疫]]由大清蔓延至香港，廣東在兩個月內就有十萬人染疫而逝<ref name="Cohn 2003 336"/>。澳門的首席醫療官員施利化博士（{{lang|pt|Gomes da Silva}}）記錄華人衛生情況時，發現他們通常將家居垃圾棄置在街上，垃圾再經夏季雨水沖去[[珠江|珠江]]。而[[香港城市大學|香港城市大學]]的研究也認為，當時本地市民的衛生問題導致疫情大規模擴散<ref>{{Cite web|title=香港早期醫療服務|url=http://www.cciv.cityu.edu.hk/website/?redirect=/field/2000-2001-b/0224B/index.php|publisher=中國文化中心|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120802004209/http://www.cciv.cityu.edu.hk/website/?redirect=/field/2000-2001-b/0224B/index.php|archivedate=2012-08-02|dead-url=yes|access-date=2020-07-22}}</ref>。[[香港總督|香港總督]][[威廉·羅便臣|威廉·羅便臣]]報告英廷時提及「二十一萬居港華人的骯髒習慣使得腺鼠疫病毒更容易入侵香港和蔓延」<ref>{{Cite journal| last = Pryor| first = E.G.| title = The Great Plague of Hong Kong| journal = Journal of the Hong Kong Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society| volume = 1975| page = 65| publisher = Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland. Hong Kong Branch (Hong Kong Branch)| location = Hong Kong| year = 1975| url = http://sunzi1.lib.hku.hk/hkjo/view/44/4401304.pdf| access-date = 2020-07-17| archive-date = 2011-06-12| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110612133432/http://sunzi1.lib.hku.hk/hkjo/view/44/4401304.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

1890年代尾，住在[[維多利亞城|維多利亞城]]的歐洲人為了遠離惡劣的生活環境，逐漸遷移至地勢更高的地方，直至高無可高的[[太平山_(香港)|太平山]]山頂。但華人人口持續膨脹，使得港英政府決定保留山頂區予歐洲人和非華人，而1904年的政府憲報強調新法例旨在回應歐洲人健康的疑慮<ref name="Jason" />。最終在1894至1929年期間，香港有24,000人染疫，當中九成人病故<ref>{{Cite journal| last = Pryor| first = E.G.| title = The Great Plague of Hong Kong| journal = Journal of the Hong Kong Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society| volume = 1975| page = 69| publisher = Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland. Hong Kong Branch (Hong Kong Branch)| location = Hong Kong| year = 1975| url = http://sunzi1.lib.hku.hk/hkjo/view/44/4401304.pdf| access-date = 2020-07-17| archive-date = 2011-06-12| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110612133432/http://sunzi1.lib.hku.hk/hkjo/view/44/4401304.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref>。瘟疫結束後的翌年，本法例正式被廢除。

=== 社會地位層面 ===
20世紀記者崔·惠瑞（{{Lang|en|Trea Wiltshire}}）在著作《舊時香港》中相信本法例的目的是社會隔離<ref>https://www.formasiabooks.com/authors/ {{Wayback|url=https://www.formasiabooks.com/authors/ |date=20200204022804 }} FormAsia authos</ref>，提出當時人的社會地位是以居所的海拔而定<ref name="Wilt" />。此法也讓上流階層能夠預留時間乘搭[[山頂纜車|山頂纜車]]<ref name="Wilt" />，例如在早上8點至10點就是讓頭等乘客搭車，即政府高層官員，讓他們可以準時返工<ref name="Wilt" />。纜車的首位預留給總督，以顯其至高社會地位，到後期更加在山頂興建了{{tsl|en|Mountain Lodge|香港總督山頂別墅|總督別墅}}避暑<ref name="Wilt" />。當時山頂區被英國人喻為「小英格蘭」<ref name="HKstory">{{cite book|last1=Courtauld|first1=Caroline|last2=Holdsworth|first2=May|title=The Hong Kong Story|publisher=Hong Kong publishing, Oxford university press|ISBN=0-19-590353-6|page=46}}</ref>，不少中上階層家庭都會有十多個華人工人<ref name="HKstory" />。

==相似法例==
香港也曾實施有關土地用途的法例，其中第一至三項均是基於種族。
*1888年《燈火及通行證條例》（{{lang|en|Light and Pass Ordinance}}）
**法例特別要求華人居民在晚上外出時，必須手攜[[燈籠|燈籠]]以及通行證<ref>{{cite book|author=Jung-fang Tsai|year=1995|title=Hong Kong in Chinese History: Community and Social Unrest in the British Colony, 1842–1913|publisher=Columbia University Press|ISBN=978-0-231-07933-4}}</ref>，相信是因為港府假定所有華人都可能是罪犯<ref>{{cite book|last1=Munn|first1=Christopher|year=2001|title=Anglo-China: Chinese People and British Rule in Hong Kong, 1841–1880|ISBN=978-0-7007-1298-4}}</ref>。
*1918年的《山頂區（住所）條例》（{{lang|en|Peak District (Residence) Ordinance}}），在1946年被廢除<ref name="Lai" /><ref name="Tubbs" /><ref name=Legco1946>{{cite web|url=http://www.legco.gov.hk/1946/h460719.pdf|title=Minutes of the meeting of the Hong Kong Legislative Council held on 19 July 1946|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031230617/https://www.legco.gov.hk/1946/h460719.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
*1919年的《長洲（住所）條例》（{{lang|en|Cheung Chau (Residence) Ordinance}}）<ref name="Lai" /><ref name="Tubbs" />，在1946年被廢除<ref name=Legco1946/>
*1888年的《歐籍區保留條例》（{{lang|en|European District Reservation Ordinance}}）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legco.gov.hk/1887-88/h880327.pdf|title=Legislative Council Report 27 March 1888|accessdate=2020-07-17|archive-date=2019-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031224438/https://www.legco.gov.hk/1887-88/h880327.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pMikv58lxdIC&pg=PA194&dq=peak+reservation+ordinance+1888+hong+kong&ei=saHiSa3-CIWqlQS_2YifDQ#PPA191,M1|title=Town planning practice|last1=Lai|first1=Lawrence Wai-Chung Lai|first2=Weicong|last2=Li|first3=Ki|last3=Fong|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811085906/https://books.google.com/books?id=pMikv58lxdIC&pg=PA194&dq=peak+reservation+ordinance+1888+hong+kong&ei=saHiSa3-CIWqlQS_2YifDQ#PPA191,M1|dead-url=no}}</ref>
**法例適用於維多利亞城城內建有[[独立式洋房|獨立式洋房]]的地帶，被視為[[德輔|德輔]]政府的城市規劃和租金管制政策。法例要求香港部分地區的建築需要遵從獨立式洋房規格，而非興建極其擠迫的中式房屋，以將地主利潤最大化。法例並不涉及種族，而只規範起樓的類型和住屋人數<ref name="Tubbs">{{Cite book| last = Tubbs, Clawson| first = Floyd R., Robert W.| authorlink = | title = Stahlhelm: Evolution of the German Steel Helmet| publisher = Kent State University Press| year = 2000| page = 15| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=1653hGljnfgC&dq=%22Hill+District+Reservation%22| isbn = 9780873386777| access-date = 2020-07-17| archive-date = 2020-08-11| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811082125/https://books.google.com/books?id=1653hGljnfgC&dq=%22Hill+District+Reservation%22| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ytg98pAFdk4C&pg=PA46&dq=European+District+Reservation+Ordinance&as_brr=3&ei=4aLiSfiAFYuIkASxlsinDQ|title=Society|first1=David|last1=Faure|access-date=2020-07-17|archive-date=2020-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724143930/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ytg98pAFdk4C&pg=PA46&dq=European+District+Reservation+Ordinance&as_brr=3&ei=4aLiSfiAFYuIkASxlsinDQ|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==豁免==
法例指出「[[行政長官會同行政會議|總督會同行政局]]認為適當的話則可豁免任何華人受此條例規限」，[[亚欧混血|歐亞混血]]富豪[[何東|何東]]爵士是首位獲香港政府准許在山頂區居住的非歐籍人士，他的家人在山腳擁有一靜居<ref name="Wilt" />。而[[中華民國大陸時期|中華民國]]第一夫人[[宋美齡|宋美齡]]也曾獲豁免<ref name="Jason"/>。

